This paper deals with deep learning approaches for magnetic resonance image (MRI) reconstruction, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a systematic geometric approach to increase the expressivity of the underlying neural network, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of attention modules, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with image reconstruction, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
